From 408a6c2094edefd993b72cbdee3b5b3878781ea3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 15:09:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: AWS-style header, repaired footer with gated social
 bar, pulsating chatbot, responsive polish
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Header (aws.amazon.com pattern):
- Compact 59px dark utility bar: logo + flat nav left; Contact Us | divider |
  Sign In | orange primary CTA right — the AWS 'Create an account' layout
- Orange underline hover on nav items; Clerk auth UI still conditional
- Mobile: dark slide-down panel with chevron rows and full-width CTAs

Footer repairs:
- Fixed broken grid (empty columns) with responsive 2/3/6-col layout
- All links now point to routes/anchors that actually exist (previous
  footer linked 8 nonexistent page anchors and 3 dead /legal routes)
- 9-platform social bar (LinkedIn, X, YouTube, Instagram, Facebook,
  TikTok, Discord, GitHub, Reddit) gated behind per-network 'enabled'
  flags: flip to true when each account is created; disabled entries
  never render, so no dead social links can ship

Chatbot:
- AWS-style pulsating attention ring + notification dot on the closed FAB
- Auto-scrolls to newest message and typing indicator
- Mobile-safe panel: full-width minus margins on phones, dvh-capped height

Responsive:
- h1 tracking relaxed and h2 scaled on <640px screens
- Button padding tuned for narrow-viewport tap targets
- Header/footer paddings adapted for small screens
